[MEN SHOUTING]

02:06.952 --> 02:08.301
-MAYDAY, MAYDAY!

02:08.431 --> 02:10.086
THIS IS THE FISHING
TRAWLER RETRIEVER.

02:10.217 --> 02:11.957
-THIS IS BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS.

02:12.088 --> 02:15.222
STATE YOUR CONDITION AND EXACT
LOCATION RETRIEVER. OVER.

02:15.352 --> 02:17.920
-WE'RE FIVE MILES DUE WEST FROM
THE PALOS VERDES PENNINSULA!

02:19.182 --> 02:20.575
SOMETHING'S CAUGHT IN OUR NETS!

02:20.705 --> 02:23.099
[TENSE MUSIC]

02:34.371 --> 02:37.505
-SAN PEDRO REPORTS
RETRIEVER HAS A SIX MAN CREW.

02:37.635 --> 02:40.072
LET'S GET 'EM ALL.
OVER. ROGER, AIRBORNE.

02:40.203 --> 02:43.989
PARAMEDICS WILL BE STANDING
BY AT SMA. TEN-FOUR.

02:44.512 --> 02:47.515
BAYWATCH RESCUE, AIRBORNE
REPORTS SMOKE PLUMES

02:47.645 --> 02:50.692
SIX K'S OVER PALOS VERDES. OVER.

02:51.519 --> 02:53.042
-ALL RIGHT, BEN, I'LL
TAKE IT FROM HERE.

02:53.173 --> 02:55.175
-CAPTAIN, YOU WANT THIS
DONE RIGHT? LET ME DO IT.

02:55.305 --> 02:56.785
-DO IT.

02:56.915 --> 02:59.222
-BAYWATCH RESCUE, THIS
IS BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS.

02:59.875 --> 03:02.269
WHAT IS YOUR TEN-TWENTY? REPEAT.

03:02.399 --> 03:05.185
BAYWATCH RESCUE, THIS IS
BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS.

03:05.315 --> 03:07.274
WHAT IS YOUR TEN-TWENTY? OVER.

03:08.927 --> 03:10.973
-SHELLY, CAN SHE GO ANY FASTER?

03:12.017 --> 03:14.759
-STAY HERE! THEY'LL
COME AND GET US!

03:14.890 --> 03:16.718
-THEIR GOONS ARE
GONNA SLOW US DOWN!

03:16.848 --> 03:17.980
-NO!

03:18.110 --> 03:19.503
-ARE YOU SET?

03:19.634 --> 03:20.983
-YEAH, BUT WHAT IF
IT'S STILL DOWN THERE?

03:21.113 --> 03:22.767
-THEN YOU'LL DIE A HERO.

03:22.898 --> 03:24.378
[FRUSTRATED YELL]

03:24.987 --> 03:26.336
-COME BACK!

03:27.337 --> 03:31.167
[SHOUTING]

03:46.008 --> 03:47.836
-MAN: I'M 20 YARDS
ON YOUR RIGHT.

03:50.708 --> 03:55.278
-OKAY, GRAB THIS! YOU GIVE
IT A COUNT OF FOUR RIGHT HERE.

03:55.409 --> 03:57.367
-LUKEY! HE'S SWIMMING TO SHORE!

03:57.498 --> 03:58.673
-WE'LL GET HIM, BUDDY.

04:00.152 --> 04:01.763
IT'S ALL RIGHT! TAKE IT EASY!

04:01.893 --> 04:05.680
[TENSE MUSIC]

04:46.808 --> 04:47.983
-YOU'VE ALL RECEIVED

04:48.113 --> 04:49.550
YOUR PRESS RELEASES
FROM DOWNTOWN.

04:49.680 --> 04:51.378
I HAVE NO FURTHER
INFORMATION AT THIS TIME.

04:51.508 --> 04:52.901
-ARE PEOPLE SAFE IN THE WATER,

04:53.031 --> 04:54.206
OR WILL YOU BE
CLOSING THE BEACHES?

04:54.337 --> 04:55.686
-WHAT ABOUT THE MARINA?

04:55.817 --> 04:57.079
-WE'RE CONSIDERING
WHAT ACTION TO TAKE.

04:57.209 --> 04:58.472
-THE NAVY HAS
SAID THAT THERE ARE

04:58.602 --> 05:00.038
NO SUBMARINES
ANYWHERE IN THAT AREA.

05:00.169 --> 05:01.866
IF IT WASN'T A SUBMARINE,

05:01.997 --> 05:03.433
COULD YOU PLEASE
TELL US WHAT IT WAS?

05:03.564 --> 05:05.696
WHAT COULD POSSIBLY
PULL A BOAT DOWN?

05:05.827 --> 05:07.307
-THAT WOULD REQUIRE
SOME SPECULATION,

05:07.437 --> 05:09.874
WHICH I AM NOT PREPARED
TO DO AT THIS TIME.

05:10.005 --> 05:11.702
[URGENT OVERLAPPING QUESTIONS]

05:13.661 --> 05:15.619
-WOULD YOU LIKE
TO KNOW THE NATURE

05:15.750 --> 05:17.578
OF THE PREDATOR
WE'RE DEALING WITH?

05:17.708 --> 05:19.406
-ALL: YES.

05:19.536 --> 05:23.148
-ITS APPETITE IS INSATIABLE.
ITS PURSUIT IS RELENTLESS.

05:23.758 --> 05:26.151
AND NO MATTER HOW
YOU TRY TO AVOID IT,

05:26.891 --> 05:29.720
IT KEEPS COMING BACK FOR MORE.

05:29.851 --> 05:32.419
-AND IT'S CALLED
'THE PRESS', RIGHT?

05:32.549 --> 05:36.510
-PRESS, PREDATOR. IT'S
PRACTICALLY THE SAME THING.

05:36.640 --> 05:39.164
NOW WE'RE TRYING TO
PROTECT THE LIVES

05:39.295 --> 05:43.255
OF 200,000 PEOPLE ON THIS BEACH.

05:44.344 --> 05:48.435
WE HAVE TO BE LET
ALONE TO DO OUR JOB.

05:49.436 --> 05:51.002
SO THANK YOU VERY
MUCH, AND GOODBYE.

05:51.133 --> 05:52.439
[REPORTERS PROTESTING]

05:52.569 --> 05:54.354
-I WILL CATCH
THIS CREATURE FOR YOU.

05:56.573 --> 05:58.445
I KNOW WHAT HE IS.

05:58.575 --> 06:01.273
[REPORTERS ASKING QUESTIONS]

06:01.404 --> 06:03.058
-MAN: WHAT DO
YOU KNOW ABOUT IT?

06:05.495 --> 06:07.628
-I'VE TRACKED HIM
ACROSS THE PACIFIC,

06:07.758 --> 06:09.543
SINCE HE MIGRATED
FROM LAKE IKEDA,

06:09.673 --> 06:11.980
KAGOSHIMA PREFECTURE,
DOWN TO THE SEA,

06:13.242 --> 06:16.419
LEAVING CARNAGE AND
DEATH IN HIS WAKE.

06:17.420 --> 06:18.769
-RELATIVE OF YOURS?

06:18.900 --> 06:20.205
-TWIN BROTHER.

06:21.772 --> 06:24.122
-THE FIRST ATTACK WAS NEAR
THE NORTH RIM OF THIS BAY.

06:24.993 --> 06:26.386
NOW, NEAR THE SOUTH RIM.

06:27.561 --> 06:29.563
HE IS MOVING TOWARD
WARMER WATERS.

06:29.693 --> 06:34.263
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

06:57.286 --> 07:01.029
-♪ BLOOD IN THE WATER- NOTHING HOTTER
'NOW THE DANGER IS REAL ♪

07:01.159 --> 07:05.033
♪ FEELING SURROUNDED- HEART IS POUNDING
THIS IS MAKING ME FEEL ♪

07:05.163 --> 07:08.689
♪ LIKE I CAN'T RIP MY EYES AWAY
FROM THE GIRLS I SEE ♪

07:08.819 --> 07:12.649
♪ THERE'S SOMETHING OUT THERE
AND IT'S TRYING TO GET A HOLD ON ME ♪

07:15.130 --> 07:16.523
♪ HOLD ON ME

07:20.570 --> 07:24.182
♪ I JUST WANNA MAKE IT- I CAN TAKE IT
IF I CAN GO WITH THE FLOW ♪

07:24.313 --> 07:27.969
♪ CAUSE IF WE'RE GONNA SWEAT IT WE'RE
GONNA LET THINGS GET OUT OF CONTROL ♪

07:28.099 --> 07:31.886
♪ I KNOW THAT THIS ISN'T THE WAY
IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE ♪

07:32.016 --> 07:36.281
♪ THERE'S SOMETHING OUT THERE
AND IT'S TRYING TO GET A HOLD ON ME ♪

07:38.370 --> 07:40.547
♪ HOLD ON ME

07:43.288 --> 07:46.901
♪ SO DON'T LOOK DOWN
IF YOU DON'T WANNA SCREAM ♪

07:47.031 --> 07:50.774
♪ THEY'VE GOT ME NOW
AND I'M NOT BREAKING FREE ♪

07:51.471 --> 07:55.083
♪ DON'T KNOW FOR SURE BUT NOW
I'M REALLY STARTING TO BELIEVE ♪

07:55.213 --> 07:58.521
♪ THERE'S SOMETHING OUT THERE
AND IT'S TRYING TO GET A HOLD OH ♪

07:58.652 --> 08:02.525
♪ ALL THESE GIRLS CAN NEVER GET ENOUGH

08:02.656 --> 08:06.486
♪ I'M JUST ONE MAN
WHO'S GONNA GIVE IT UP ♪

08:06.616 --> 08:10.359
♪ DON'T KNOW FOR SURE BUT NOW
I'M REALLY STARTING TO BELIEVE ♪

08:10.490 --> 08:14.319
♪ THERE'S SOMETHING OUT THERE
AND IT'S TRYING TO GET A HOLD ON ME ♪

08:47.091 --> 08:50.094
[CUTLERY CLINKING]

08:51.226 --> 08:53.271
-YOU KNOW, THE CUISINE
MAY NOT BE THE BEST IN TOWN,

08:53.837 --> 08:55.186
BUT LINDA, I
FIGURED AT LEAST YOU

08:55.317 --> 08:57.319
WOULDN'T BE HASSLED
BY REPORTERS HERE.

09:01.192 --> 09:03.543
-GUESS THAT MEANS
YOU'VE SAVED ME TWICE.

09:08.199 --> 09:09.592
-LINDA, I TRIED TO ARRANGE

09:09.723 --> 09:11.463
FOR YOU TO STAY ON
DEVON'S HOUSEBOAT.

09:11.594 --> 09:13.814
-NO, I'M GLAD--
I'M GLAD I'M HERE, ACTUALLY.

09:13.944 --> 09:15.467
I FEEL VERY COMFORTABLE HERE.

09:15.598 --> 09:16.991
-GOOD, I'M GLAD.

09:19.733 --> 09:21.604
-DON'T FREAK IF THE
SMOKE ALARM GOES OFF.

09:21.735 --> 09:24.259
DAD LIKES TO TEST IT
EVERY NOW AND THEN.

09:25.216 --> 09:26.609
-HEARD THAT.

09:28.698 --> 09:31.614
-SO, THE TWO OF
YOU LIVE HERE ALONE?

09:31.745 --> 09:33.877
-SINCE MOM AND DAD GOT
DIVORCED TWO YEARS AGO.

09:34.008 --> 09:35.575
SHE LIVES IN OHIO NOW.

09:37.098 --> 09:39.274
-SO, THAT MEANS YOU GET
TO LIVE WITH YOUR DAD.

09:39.970 --> 09:41.493
-YEAH, BUT MOM
WORRIES I'LL GROW UP

09:41.624 --> 09:42.930
TO BE TOO MUCH LIKE
HIM, SO I HAVE TO

09:43.060 --> 09:45.019
GO AND VISIT HER AS
MUCH AS POSSIBLE.

09:45.149 --> 09:46.760
-WELL, LET ME TELL YOU.
GROWING UP LIKE YOUR DAD

09:46.890 --> 09:47.891
WOULDN'T BE SO
TERRIBLE, YOU KNOW?

09:48.022 --> 09:50.894
-I KNOW. HE'S A GREAT GUY.

09:52.548 --> 09:55.464
CAN I ASK YOU ABOUT
WHAT, YOU KNOW.

09:55.595 --> 09:57.161
LIKE, WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU?

09:57.292 --> 09:58.598
I MEAN, IF YOU DON'T MIND.

09:58.728 --> 10:00.208
IF YOU DON'T WANNA
TALK, THAT'S OKAY.

10:00.338 --> 10:02.776
-OH NO, THAT'S FINE.
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO KNOW?

10:02.906 --> 10:04.734
-THE THING YOU SAW.

10:05.648 --> 10:10.218
IT DIDN'T LOOK ANYTHING
LIKE THIS, DID IT?

10:11.219 --> 10:12.524
[LAUGHTER]

10:13.395 --> 10:15.789
-NO, I MEAN, IF THAT'S
WHAT YOUR DAD SAID

10:15.919 --> 10:18.574
THAT IT WAS THEN THAT'S
WHAT IT MUST HAVE BEEN.

10:18.705 --> 10:21.621
-WHAT? HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY!

10:21.751 --> 10:22.622
LET ME SEE THAT.

10:22.752 --> 10:24.449
-[LAUGHS]

10:24.580 --> 10:27.409
-TOXIC MUTANT
JELLYFISH WITH LEGS?

10:27.539 --> 10:28.889
JELLYFISH DON'T HAVE LEGS.

10:29.019 --> 10:30.934
-SO? NO ONE'S SAFE,
EVEN ON DRY LAND.

10:31.065 --> 10:33.284
-HARVEY WON'T BE SAFE
WHEN I GET MY HANDS ON HIM.

10:33.415 --> 10:34.895
-HE SOLD HUNDREDS OF THEM, DAD.

10:35.025 --> 10:36.592
HE'S PRINTING UP 5,000 MORE.

10:36.723 --> 10:38.986
THIS MONSTER IN THE BAY'S
THE MOST RADICAL THING

10:39.116 --> 10:40.683
THAT'S HAPPENED AT
THE BEACH IN YEARS.

10:41.641 --> 10:44.426
-LINDA. WE'RE SORRY.
HE WAS JUST KIDDING AROUND.

10:44.556 --> 10:45.949
-AH, THAT'S OKAY.

10:46.080 --> 10:47.298
ACTUALLY, IT FELT GOOD
TO LAUGH ABOUT IT.

10:47.429 --> 10:49.213
I MEAN, WHO KNOWS?

10:49.344 --> 10:52.260
MAYBE IT WAS A MUTANT
JELLYFISH, OR SOMETHING.

10:52.390 --> 10:54.131
-I DON'T THINK SO.
YOU KNOW WHAT I THINK IT WAS?

10:54.262 --> 10:55.524
-SAVE IT.

10:56.177 --> 10:57.918
-GO AHEAD, HOBIE.
WHAT DO YOU THINK IT WAS?

10:58.048 --> 11:01.617
-ALIENS! YOU KNOW, LIKE IN
THE ABYSS, LIVING DOWN THERE.

11:01.748 --> 11:04.446
-ALIENS?
-I MEAN, IF THEY WERE
HERE ON THIS PLANET,

11:04.576 --> 11:07.841
THAT'S A LOGICAL PLACE FOR
THEM TO HIDE, UNDER THE OCEAN.

11:08.972 --> 11:10.800
-HE'S SEEN WAY TOO MANY VIDEOS.

11:10.931 --> 11:13.673
-YOU'RE THE ONE WHO RENTS
THOSE GROSS MONSTER MOVIES,

11:13.803 --> 11:16.240
LIKE THE BEAST
FROM 20,000 FATHOMS

11:16.371 --> 11:18.678
AND THE CREATURE FROM
THE BLACK LAGOON.

11:18.808 --> 11:20.288
-YEAH, BUT I KNOW
THE DIFFERENCE

11:20.418 --> 11:22.246
BETWEEN MOVIES AND
REAL LIFE, PAL.

11:22.377 --> 11:25.902
[SIZZLING]

11:26.033 --> 11:28.905
[FIRM ALARM BEEPING]

11:39.046 --> 11:40.308
-GOTTA LOVE HIM.

11:47.228 --> 11:50.579
[SOFT SOBBING]

12:08.858 --> 12:12.122
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

12:24.178 --> 12:25.048
-YOU ALL RIGHT?

12:26.702 --> 12:28.269
-OH, I'M SORRY, DID I WAKE YOU?

12:29.052 --> 12:33.274
-NO. NO, I WAS JUST
HAVING A BIZARRE DREAM.

12:34.057 --> 12:35.363
-REALLY? ABOUT WHAT?

12:37.582 --> 12:40.455
-OLD MOVIES. STUPID STUFF.

12:41.151 --> 12:42.326
-I LOVE OLD MOVIES.

12:42.457 --> 12:45.329
YOU KNOW, LIKE,
WUTHERING HEIGHTS.

12:46.548 --> 12:52.206
I USED TO PRETEND THAT I
WAS CATHY AND, YOU KNOW,

12:52.336 --> 12:55.252
YOU LOOK AN AWFUL LOT LIKE
HEATHCLIFF IN THAT MOVIE.

12:55.383 --> 12:57.298
-YOU BETTER GO BACK TO BED.

12:58.734 --> 12:59.953
-I CAN'T SLEEP.

13:00.954 --> 13:03.826
-COME ON. I'LL TUCK
YOU IN HOBIE'S BED

13:03.957 --> 13:05.567
AND I'LL GIVE YOU ONE
OF HIS STUFFED ANIMALS

13:05.697 --> 13:07.787
AND I GUARANTEE YOU,
YOU'LL BE OUT LIKE A LIGHT.

13:09.005 --> 13:10.615
-IS THAT HOW YOU GET
HOBIE TO GO TO SLEEP?

13:11.225 --> 13:12.922
-WELL, SOMETIMES
I RUB HIS BACK.

13:14.184 --> 13:15.446
-WOULD YOU RUB MY BACK?

13:17.535 --> 13:19.363
-SURE, SURE.

13:20.930 --> 13:25.935
[SENSUAL MUSIC]

13:43.039 --> 13:44.388
-THAT FEELS GREAT.

13:59.360 --> 14:00.840
-LINDA.

14:01.666 --> 14:02.580
-YOU DON'T HAVE TO STOP.

14:02.711 --> 14:04.800
-YEAH, YEAH I DO. I DO.

14:07.890 --> 14:10.066
YOU'RE A REALLY
BEAUTIFUL WOMAN, AND.

14:11.372 --> 14:13.678
WELL, UNDER ANY
OTHER CIRCUMSTANCES

14:15.767 --> 14:17.987
I KNOW THIS WOULD BE
THE START OF SOMETHING.

14:19.119 --> 14:20.772
BUT TONIGHT'S GOTTA BE THE END.

14:20.903 --> 14:23.471
-WELL, THIS ISN'T A
REWARD FOR YOU SAVING ME.

14:23.601 --> 14:26.082
I MEAN, I'D WANT YOU,

14:26.213 --> 14:28.432
EVEN IF YOU DIDN'T RESCUE ME.

14:28.563 --> 14:30.913
-LINDA, LOOK, I'M
USING EVERY OUNCE

14:31.044 --> 14:33.568
OF WILLPOWER I HAVE
HERE, BELIEVE ME.

14:33.698 --> 14:38.312
ANOTHER 30 SECONDS, I'M GONNA
HATE MYSELF IN THE MORNING.

14:40.096 --> 14:40.880
OKAY?

14:41.010 --> 14:41.881
-OKAY.

14:43.143 --> 14:47.147
WELL, SO, WOULD YOU
STILL TUCK ME IN?

14:48.713 --> 14:52.065
-YEAH. COME ON.

14:52.195 --> 14:53.109
-OKAY.

14:55.198 --> 14:56.156
-WHEW.

14:57.418 --> 15:00.595
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

15:15.740 --> 15:17.046
-WHAT ABOUT A WHALE?

15:18.047 --> 15:20.615
-POSSIBLY, BUT THAT DOESN'T
EXPLAIN THE CORONER'S REPORT.

15:20.745 --> 15:22.356
IT SAID THAT WALT WAS CRUSHED BY

15:22.486 --> 15:24.445
SOMETHING POWERFUL THAT
DIDN'T PIERCE HIS SKIN.

15:24.575 --> 15:27.056
NOW, THAT WOULD ELIMINATE
A WHALE OR A SHARK.

15:27.187 --> 15:28.188
-MAYBE I WAS RIGHT.

15:28.318 --> 15:29.580
-WHAT?

15:29.711 --> 15:32.061
-MAYBE IT WAS A
MUTANT, TOXIC JELLYFISH.

15:34.194 --> 15:36.196
-YOU GUYS ARE NOT
GONNA BELIEVE THIS.

15:36.326 --> 15:37.327
[SIRENS]

15:37.458 --> 15:38.372
[GUNSHOT]

15:46.771 --> 15:49.078
-I GOT IT. WHAT'S GOING ON?

15:49.209 --> 15:50.601
-HE GOT TWO OR THREE SHOTS OFF

15:50.732 --> 15:51.994
INTO THE STORM DRAIN
BEFORE I COULD STOP HIM.

15:52.125 --> 15:53.561
-PUT HIM IN
TEMPORARY RESTRAINTS

15:53.691 --> 15:54.779
AND HOLD HIM UNTIL
THE POLICE GET HERE.

15:54.910 --> 15:56.564
-MITCH, CHECK THIS OUT.

15:57.608 --> 15:59.306
-TAKE THIS, WILL YA?
GIVE ME YOUR FLASHLIGHT.

15:59.436 --> 16:00.481
GET SOME CROWD CONTROL IN HERE.

16:00.611 --> 16:01.786
-OKAY.

16:01.917 --> 16:03.353
-WHATCHA GOT?

16:03.484 --> 16:05.921
-FOOTPRINTS, A TAIL
DRAGGING BETWEEN THEM.

16:06.052 --> 16:07.314
IT'S GOTTA BE A HOAX.

16:10.056 --> 16:11.492
HEY, YOU'RE TRAMPLING
THE VERY THING

16:11.622 --> 16:12.797
YOU WANT TO GET YOUR STORY ON.

16:12.928 --> 16:14.321
-BETTER KEEP ONE
OF THESE INTACT

16:14.451 --> 16:16.236
IN CASE THE POLICE WANT
A PLASTER CAST OF IT.

16:16.366 --> 16:17.280
-YEAH, OKAY.

16:18.020 --> 16:19.848
-EXCUSE ME. STAY
OUT OF THE DRAINS.

16:19.979 --> 16:24.070
[OVERLAPPING SHOUTING]

16:24.200 --> 16:26.420
-WHAT KIND OF PREDATOR
ARE YOU UP AGAINST NOW?

16:26.550 --> 16:28.074
-EXCUSE ME, WOULD
YOU ALL BE QUIET?

16:28.204 --> 16:30.815
BACK 'EM UP, PLEASE.
PUT YOUR CAMERAS DOWN.

16:31.816 --> 16:33.035
SHUT UP, WILL YA!

16:33.166 --> 16:34.950
-WAIT! WE NEED THE EXPLOSIVES.

16:35.081 --> 16:36.430
WE MUST BURY IT
IN THERE FOREVER!

16:36.560 --> 16:37.822
-WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?

16:37.953 --> 16:38.998
HEINZ, GET THIS
CHARACTER OUT OF HERE

16:39.128 --> 16:40.695
AND CHECK WHAT'S
IN THE KNAPSACK.

16:42.436 --> 16:43.741
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

16:44.351 --> 16:46.831
[LOUD ROAR]

16:56.276 --> 16:59.670
[EERIE MUSIC]

16:59.801 --> 17:02.543
[DRIPPING WATER]

17:02.673 --> 17:06.851
[ECHOING ROAR]

17:16.035 --> 17:21.127
[LOUDER ROAR]

17:23.477 --> 17:25.044
[STARTLED GASP]

17:26.522 --> 17:28.221
-WELL, I DIDN'T
THINK YOU MEANT ME.

17:28.351 --> 17:29.657
-WHAT?

17:29.787 --> 17:31.093
-WHEN YOU TOLD EVERYONE
TO WAIT OUTSIDE.

17:31.833 --> 17:32.790
-OH.

17:34.096 --> 17:38.318
[ANIMAL GROWL]

17:44.324 --> 17:47.936
[ANIMAL ROAR]

17:57.554 --> 18:00.122
[WORRIED MURMURING]

18:01.689 --> 18:03.082
-NOW, THE QUESTION IS:

18:03.212 --> 18:05.649
HOW MUCH DO WE TRUST
OUR RATIONAL MINDS?

18:06.607 --> 18:07.999
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

18:08.130 --> 18:09.305
-I'M TRYING TO DECIDE IF

18:09.436 --> 18:11.046
I'M ASLEEP OR DREAMING THIS.

18:11.177 --> 18:13.222
-TRUST ME,
MITCH, YOU'RE AWAKE.

18:14.354 --> 18:16.138
-THAT'S EXACTLY WHAT YOU'D
SAY IF I WAS DREAMING.

18:16.269 --> 18:19.359
-FINE, THEN WAKE UP, AND
LET'S GET THE HELL OUTTA HERE.

18:19.489 --> 18:21.230
-THE PROBLEM IS,
WITH DREAMS LIKE THIS,

18:22.579 --> 18:23.972
I USUALLY DON'T WAKE UP

18:24.103 --> 18:25.147
UNTIL SOMETHING SCARES
THE HELL OUTTA ME.

18:25.278 --> 18:30.196
[LOAD ROAR]

18:30.326 --> 18:31.719
-UH, AFTER YOU.

18:34.069 --> 18:35.592
-I'M DEFINITELY AWAKE.

18:35.723 --> 18:37.333
-HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT?

18:37.464 --> 18:40.336
-BECAUSE IF I WAS DREAMING,
I'D SEND YOU IN FIRST.

18:45.341 --> 18:47.996
[ECHOING ROAR]

18:54.133 --> 18:56.874
-GOTCHA! I GOTCHA!
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT,

18:57.005 --> 18:58.441
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU FELL FOR IT!

18:58.572 --> 19:00.922
-HOBIE! DAMMIT, YOU COULD
HAVE BEEN KILLED!

19:02.532 --> 19:05.013
-DON'T HAVE A COW, DAD.
IT WAS JUST A JOKE.

19:05.144 --> 19:06.493
THEY'RE TAPES FROM
OLD MONSTER MOVIES.

19:06.623 --> 19:08.059
DIDN'T YOU RECOGNIZE 'EM?

19:08.190 --> 19:09.887
-YOU HAVE TO ADMIT,
MITCH, IT WAS CLEVER.

19:10.018 --> 19:11.324
HE HAD US ALL GOING.

19:11.454 --> 19:13.369
-YEAH, CLEVER, BUT
NOT FUNNY AT ALL.

19:13.500 --> 19:14.936
DID YOU HEAR THOSE
SHOTS OUTSIDE?

19:15.066 --> 19:16.590
THAT WAS SOME NUT WITH A RIFLE.

19:16.720 --> 19:18.026
HE COULD HAVE SHOT YOU, PAL.

19:19.070 --> 19:20.768
-I THOUGHT I'D SCARE SOME KIDS.

19:20.898 --> 19:23.249
I DIDN'T EXPECT A WHOLE BUNCH
OF GROWNUPS TO BELIEVE IT.

19:23.379 --> 19:24.728
ESPECIALLY YOU, DAD.

19:24.859 --> 19:26.382
-WHAT ARE YOU EVEN
DOING DOWN HERE, ANYWAY?

19:26.513 --> 19:27.427
YOU'RE SUPPOSED
TO BE WITH LINDA.

19:27.557 --> 19:28.515
WHERE IS SHE?

19:28.645 --> 19:29.777
-SHE WENT BACK TO VIRGINIA.

19:30.473 --> 19:31.692
SHE LEFT YOU A NOTE.

19:40.831 --> 19:42.050
-IF YOU
LOOK ON THE MANTLE,

19:42.181 --> 19:43.617
YOU'LL SEE A PICTURE
OF YOU MISSING.

19:45.140 --> 19:46.968
I TOOK IT SO I CAN
LOOK INTO YOUR EYES

19:47.098 --> 19:48.970
AND REMEMBER HOW YOU CALMED ME.

19:50.450 --> 19:52.713
THINK OF ME NEXT TIME
YOU RUB HOBIE'S BACK.

19:59.198 --> 20:02.723
-DAD, CAN I SLEEP IN
YOUR ROOM AGAIN TONIGHT?

20:02.853 --> 20:04.681
-NO. GO BACK TO BED.

20:04.812 --> 20:06.161
-BUT I SAID I WAS SORRY.

20:06.292 --> 20:08.076
-I APPRECIATE THAT,
BUT YOU'RE STAYING

20:08.207 --> 20:09.469
IN YOUR OWN ROOM TONIGHT.

20:09.599 --> 20:11.601
-I APPRECIATE
THAT, BUT YOU KNOW,

20:11.732 --> 20:14.125
IF I WAS SOME KID YOU
RESCUED INSTEAD OF YOUR SON,

20:14.256 --> 20:17.085
YOU WOULDN'T LET ME BE ALONE
UNTIL YOU WERE SURE I WAS OKAY.

20:19.435 --> 20:20.393
-YOU'RE RIGHT. GO ON.

20:20.523 --> 20:21.698
-THANKS, DAD!

20:21.829 --> 20:23.352
-HEY, HEY,
HEY, WAIT A MINUTE.

20:23.483 --> 20:25.354
DON'T ACT LIKE YOU JUST
WON A MAJOR VICTORY, HERE.

20:25.485 --> 20:26.399
YOU'RE STILL
GROUNDED FOR A MONTH,

20:26.529 --> 20:27.443
AND I'M STILL MAD AT YOU.

20:27.574 --> 20:29.358
-I'M STILL MAD AT YOU.

20:29.489 --> 20:31.534
-YOU'RE MAD AT ME? WHY?

20:31.665 --> 20:33.623
-FOR HAVING DEVON SNEAK
US OUT THE BACK WAY

20:33.754 --> 20:35.321
AND TELLING THOSE
REPORTERS NO ONE WAS THERE

20:35.451 --> 20:37.061
WHEN YOU FOUND MY GADGETS.

20:38.062 --> 20:39.455
I COULD HAVE BEEN FAMOUS, DAD.

20:39.586 --> 20:41.152
-ALL RIGHT, LET'S GET
ONE THING STRAIGHT.

20:42.110 --> 20:44.155
WHAT YOU DID WAS
DANGEROUS AND DUMB.

20:44.808 --> 20:46.897
A MAN'S BEEN KILLED,
BOATS HAVE BEEN SUNK,

20:47.028 --> 20:48.377
SOME LUNATIC WAS READY TO

20:48.508 --> 20:50.205
BLOW UP THE STORM
DRAIN WITH YOU IN IT.

20:50.336 --> 20:52.512
THERE'S NO TIME FOR A
PRACTICAL JOKE, HOBIE.

20:52.642 --> 20:54.296
NO MATTER HOW CLEVER.

20:58.474 --> 21:00.041
COME HERE. SIT DOWN.

21:04.567 --> 21:07.570
LOOK, I KNOW YOU WERE
JUST BEING TEN YEARS OLD,

21:10.878 --> 21:13.097
BUT IF ANYTHING EVER
HAPPENED TO YOU, MAN,

21:14.142 --> 21:15.535
I DON'T KNOW WHAT I'D DO.

21:19.103 --> 21:20.540
COULDN'T LIVE WITHOUT YOU.

21:24.152 --> 21:25.545
-I'M REALLY SORRY.

21:27.938 --> 21:30.201
-JUST USE YOUR HEAD
FROM NOW ON, OKAY?

21:30.332 --> 21:31.115
-I WILL.

21:31.246 --> 21:32.116
-OKAY.

21:32.247 --> 21:35.381
-I SWEAR. DAD?

21:36.599 --> 21:37.644
-YEAH?

21:38.819 --> 21:40.037
-I LOVE YOU.

21:42.126 --> 21:43.302
-I LOVE YOU, TOO.

21:47.784 --> 21:49.438
-FIRST OF ALL,
I'D LIKE TO START OFF

21:49.569 --> 21:51.397
BY SAYING CONGRATULATIONS
TO EVERYONE HERE.

21:51.527 --> 21:53.268
YOU'RE ALL NOW OFFICIAL MEMBERS

21:53.399 --> 21:55.618
OF THE LA COUNTRY
LIFEGUARD'S WATER PROGRAM.

21:56.837 --> 21:59.883
NOW, THE OCEAN. VERY POWERFUL.

22:00.797 --> 22:02.451
BEING IN IT CAN BE
A LITTLE BIT SCARY.

22:02.582 --> 22:04.279
OR, IT CAN BE EXCITING.

22:04.932 --> 22:06.760
WE'RE GONNA MAKE IT
EXCITING FOR YOU, NOT SCARY.

22:07.500 --> 22:08.805
ALL RIGHT, WE'RE GONNA START

22:08.936 --> 22:09.980
BY HAVING YOU GET
USED TO THE WAVES.

22:10.111 --> 22:11.417
LET'S GO. COME ON.

22:11.547 --> 22:15.246
[CHILDREN YELLING EXCITEDLY]

22:26.127 --> 22:27.781
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE, HUH?

22:28.608 --> 22:30.871
YOU GUYS AREN'T AFRAID
OF SEA MONSTERS, ARE YOU?

22:31.001 --> 22:32.873
-I'D DRILL HIM IF
HE TRIED TO GET ME.

22:35.571 --> 22:36.877
-TIANA, YOU DON'T
HAVE TO BE AFRAID

22:37.007 --> 22:38.226
BECAUSE I'M GONNA
BE WITH YOU, OKAY?

22:38.357 --> 22:39.575
-OKAY.

22:40.315 --> 22:42.491
BUT LAST TIME I
COULDN'T SWIM BACK IN.

22:42.622 --> 22:44.798
-WELL, THAT'S BECAUSE YOU
GOT CAUGHT IN A RIPTIDE.

22:45.581 --> 22:47.061
-WHAT MAKES IT?

22:47.191 --> 22:50.499
-WELL, A RIPTIDE IS
WHEN THE WAVES PUT

22:50.630 --> 22:52.545
A LOT OF WATER ON THE
BEACH AND SOMETIMES

22:52.675 --> 22:54.808
THAT FORMS A RIVER,
AND IT RUSHES OUT.

22:55.417 --> 22:56.723
NOW, IF YOU GET
CAUGHT IN THAT RIVER,

22:56.853 --> 22:58.594
YOU'LL RUSH OUT WITH IT.

22:58.725 --> 23:01.292
BUT YOU SEE, THE TRICK IS TO
NOT SWIM THROUGH A RIPTIDE,

23:01.423 --> 23:03.817
TO SWIM SIDEWAYS UNTIL
YOU'RE OUT OF IT.

23:03.947 --> 23:05.732
BUT YOU DON'T HAVE TO
WORRY ABOUT THAT, OKAY?

23:06.515 --> 23:08.169
THERE ARE NO RIPTIDES
OUT THERE RIGHT NOW

23:08.299 --> 23:09.736
AND YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
A LOT OF FUN, OKAY?

23:09.866 --> 23:10.867
TRUST ME.

23:12.434 --> 23:14.610
-SHANI, WILL YOU HOLD
MY HAND IN THE WATER?

23:15.219 --> 23:20.137
SHAUNI? SHAUNI?

23:20.268 --> 23:22.749
-WHAT? OH, OF COURSE I WILL.

23:22.879 --> 23:24.185
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?

23:24.315 --> 23:25.534
FIRST I HAVE TO GO
TALK TO SOMEBODY,

23:25.665 --> 23:27.057
AND THEN I'LL BE
RIGHT BACK, OKAY?

23:27.188 --> 23:28.058
EDDIE'S GONNA HOLD
YOUR HAND UNTIL THEN.

23:28.189 --> 23:28.972
-OKAY.

23:29.103 --> 23:30.104
-OKAY.

23:30.234 --> 23:31.279
-OKAY.

23:38.242 --> 23:39.635
-WHO'S THAT?

23:40.636 --> 23:41.811
-HER FATHER.

23:42.551 --> 23:43.726
-OH.

24:01.091 --> 24:02.310
-WHAT'S GOING ON DOWN THERE?

24:03.354 --> 24:04.921
LIFESAVING CLASSES OR SOMETHING?

24:05.922 --> 24:08.098
-WE RUN A PROGRAM
FOR INNER CITY KIDS.

24:09.796 --> 24:10.797
-THAT'S COMMENDABLE.

24:11.711 --> 24:12.929
-WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE, DADDY?

24:14.670 --> 24:16.106
-WELL, I CAME
DOWN HERE TO TALK--

24:17.499 --> 24:19.066
SHANI, WOULD YOU PLEASE TRY

24:19.196 --> 24:20.937
TO LOOK AT ME WHEN
I'M SPEAKING TO YOU?

24:21.068 --> 24:22.852
-I HAVE TO WATCH THE WATER.

24:25.202 --> 24:26.726
SO, WHY ARE YOU HERE?

24:28.554 --> 24:30.077
-NO, WHY ARE YOU HERE?

24:30.207 --> 24:31.644
-BECAUSE I WORK HERE.

24:31.774 --> 24:33.036
-WELL YOU CERTAINLY
DON'T NEED THE MONEY.

24:35.169 --> 24:39.695
SHANI. LOOK, I COULD FOLLOW
YOU OFF THE BEACH AT NIGHT.

24:41.001 --> 24:42.611
THIS COULD BE A VERY
DANGEROUS PLACE.

24:42.742 --> 24:44.874
-THAT'S RIGHT, IT
CAN BE DANGEROUS.

24:45.005 --> 24:47.224
YOU SEE THAT LITTLE GIRL
OVER THERE WITH EDDIE?

24:47.355 --> 24:48.704
-YEAH, WHAT ABOUT HER?

24:49.488 --> 24:51.272
-WELL, I SAVED HER LIFE.

24:52.491 --> 24:55.145
SHE WAS DROWNING. SHE WAS
COMPLETELY SUBMERGED UNDER WATER

24:55.276 --> 24:57.887
AND SHE STOPPED BREATHING AND
I BREATHED LIFE BACK INTO HER.

24:59.541 --> 25:01.587
AND IF I HADN'T BEEN
THERE, SHE'D HAVE DIED.

25:05.373 --> 25:07.288
-WELL, WHY DIDN'T YOU
TELL YOUR MOTHER AND ME?

25:10.378 --> 25:11.553
-I DON'T KNOW.

25:15.209 --> 25:17.167
YOU KNOW, YOU USED
TO GIVE ME $50

25:17.298 --> 25:18.865
FOR EVERY A IN MY REPORT CARD.

25:20.910 --> 25:23.870
BUT I NEVER ONCE FELT
LIKE YOU WERE PROUD OF ME.

25:24.479 --> 25:26.307
-IF YOU'D HAVE TOLD US THAT YOU

25:26.437 --> 25:28.004
ACTUALLY SAVED SOMEBODY'S LIFE.

25:28.135 --> 25:29.702
-WHAT DO YOU THINK
WE DO HERE ALL DAY?

25:29.832 --> 25:31.051
WORK ON OUR TANS?

25:31.181 --> 25:32.748
I GOTTA GO BACK TO WORK.

25:32.879 --> 25:35.142
-SHAUNI! SHAUNI, WAIT!

25:40.626 --> 25:42.105
YOU KNOW, WHEN YOU WERE LITTLE,

25:44.499 --> 25:48.372
I USED TO WORRY ABOUT
HOW I'D HANDLE IT

25:48.503 --> 25:52.942
WHEN YOU BECAME A YOUNG WOMAN.

25:56.816 --> 26:02.735
I KNEW I'D KILL ANY GUY
WHO DIDN'T TREAT YOU

26:02.865 --> 26:05.346
WITH THE KIND OF
RESPECT YOU DESERVE.

26:08.175 --> 26:12.179
NOW I GUESS I'M GUILTY
OF DOING JUST THAT.

26:16.052 --> 26:20.056
SHANI, I'M VERY PROUD OF YOU.

26:25.801 --> 26:27.586
I DON'T KNOW WHAT ELSE TO SAY.

26:32.808 --> 26:34.027
-THANK YOU.

26:38.248 --> 26:39.380
I HAVE TO GO.

26:52.785 --> 26:54.264
[SNIFF]

26:57.659 --> 26:59.443
-RAY, IF YOU
PUBLISH THOSE PHOTOGRAPHS,

26:59.574 --> 27:01.576
I SWEAR I'LL QUIT.

27:03.056 --> 27:07.103
WHAT? NO, I'M AT PETROVISION.

27:07.887 --> 27:09.976
TO INTERVIEW VAN ALDEN.

27:11.064 --> 27:13.588
BECAUSE THE BIDDING ON THE
OFFSHORE OIL LEASES IS UP

27:13.719 --> 27:16.678
NEXT WEEK, AND I HAVEN'T EVEN
FINISHED MY ORIGINAL STORY.

27:16.809 --> 27:18.071
RAY, I HAVE TO GO.

27:18.898 --> 27:20.464
NO, DON'T YOU DARE
PUBLISH THOSE PHOTOGRAPHS

27:20.595 --> 27:21.814
WITHOUT MY PERMISSION.

27:27.776 --> 27:32.476
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

27:48.449 --> 27:50.059
-HOW'S IT HANGING, BEN?

27:50.190 --> 27:52.148
-PRETTY CROOKED, RIGHT
NOW, I'M SITTING HERE

27:52.279 --> 27:53.715
AND ALL THE ACTION'S OUT THERE.

27:54.847 --> 27:56.413
NOW, WAIT A MINUTE.

27:56.544 --> 27:58.633
MITCH IS BUSY, HE DOESN'T
WANT TO BE DISTURBED.

27:58.764 --> 28:00.853
-OH, I'M SURE HE'LL WANT
TO BE DISTURBED FOR THIS.

28:00.983 --> 28:02.463
-PATIENCE IS A VIRTUE.

28:03.116 --> 28:05.553
-THAT IT IS, BEN.
SO DON'T TRY MINE.

28:06.380 --> 28:09.426
-WHY NOT? YOU'VE BEEN
TRYING MINE FOR 20 YEARS.

28:10.427 --> 28:11.864
-CHAIN OF COMMAND, BEN.

28:11.994 --> 28:14.388
MOVING UP THE RANKS IS A
STEP BY STEP PROCEDURE.

28:16.085 --> 28:17.913
-I KNOW YOU CAN'T
PROMOTE ME TO CAPTAIN.

28:19.480 --> 28:20.699
I GET THAT.

28:22.744 --> 28:24.180
BUT WHAT I DON'T
GET IS YOU PUTTING

28:24.311 --> 28:26.139
ALL YOUR CHESS PLAYERS
ON THEIR OWN SQUARES.

28:26.269 --> 28:28.315
YOU'VE GOTTA HATE
IT DOWNTOWN, CAP.

28:28.445 --> 28:29.577
AND YOU KNOW IT.

28:31.622 --> 28:36.932
STAY HERE AS A CAPTAIN, YOU
PROMOTE ME TO LIEUTENANT.

28:38.542 --> 28:40.980
THAT FREES MITCH TO
DO WHAT HE DOES BEST.

28:42.155 --> 28:45.724
PATROLS THE SAND, HE HITS THE
WATER, HE MAKES THE BIG RESCUE

28:47.160 --> 28:50.032
WINNING CHESS IS
NOT ABOUT AMBITION.

28:50.641 --> 28:55.124
IT'S ABOUT SOUND STRATEGY. SO?

28:55.255 --> 28:59.738
-SO, I'LL TAKE IT
UNDER ADVISEMENT, BEN.

29:04.960 --> 29:06.135
-TADASHI?

29:06.832 --> 29:08.398
WHAT WOULD SOME
LUNATIC LIKE TADASHI

29:08.529 --> 29:09.878
BEING DOING WITH VAN ALDEN?
-WELL, I DON'T KNOW.

29:10.009 --> 29:11.445
MAYBE HE'S PAYING
HIM THE 50 GRAND

29:11.575 --> 29:13.186
TO MAKE SURE NOTHING
DEVOURS HIS OIL WELLS.

29:13.316 --> 29:15.101
-YEAH, RIGHT.

29:15.231 --> 29:16.972
YOU DIDN'T BY ANY CHANCE GET
HIS LICENSE NUMBER, DID YOU?

29:17.103 --> 29:18.757
-THAT I DID.

29:18.887 --> 29:20.497
BUT I QUIT THE PAPER
BEFORE I HAD THE CHANCE

29:20.628 --> 29:22.064
TO USE THE CONTACTS TO TRACE IT.

29:28.070 --> 29:30.377
MITCH, I'M SORRY ABOUT THOSE
PHOTOS WE HAD PUBLISHED.

29:30.507 --> 29:32.727
I JUST HOPE THEY DON'T
COMPLICATE YOUR LIFE TOO MUCH.

29:32.858 --> 29:35.730
-[WRY LAUGH]
MY LIFE COMPLICATED? NEVER.

29:35.861 --> 29:39.081
-MITCH. LISTEN TO THIS.

29:39.212 --> 29:40.909
-HANG ON ONE SECOND.

29:41.040 --> 29:46.523
BEN, SEE IF YOU CAN GET A
LICENSE NUMBER FOR 36780C6.

29:46.654 --> 29:50.049
YEAH, THANKS. WHAT DO YOU GOT?

29:50.179 --> 29:51.920
-THEY COULDN'T DETERMINE
WHAT CUT THROUGH THE NETS,

29:52.051 --> 29:53.922
BUT THEY DID HAVE SOMETHING
VERY INTERESTING TO SAY

29:54.053 --> 29:56.011
ABOUT THE CAVE IN
LINDA'S PHOTOGRAPHS.

29:58.622 --> 29:59.754
-I'LL LEAVE IF YOU'D LIKE.

29:59.885 --> 30:01.887
-NO, IT'S OKAY,
SHE'S ON OUR SIDE.

30:02.017 --> 30:03.279
YOU'RE GONNA NEED
A GOOD EXCLUSIVE

30:03.410 --> 30:04.454
IF YOU WANT THAT
JOB AT THE TIMES.

30:04.585 --> 30:05.542
-THANK YOU.

30:07.631 --> 30:09.372
-THE CAVE IS NOT A
NATURAL FORMATION.

30:09.503 --> 30:11.244
IT WAS DRILLED OUT OF THE ROCKS.

30:12.158 --> 30:13.724
-YOU KNOW, IF THERE'S
A PARTY GOING ON IN HERE

30:13.855 --> 30:15.944
I CERTAINLY THINK I
SHOULD HAVE BEEN INVITED.

30:16.075 --> 30:18.164
ESPECIALLY CONSIDERING I'M
THE ONE WHO BROUGHT THE GIFT.

30:18.294 --> 30:19.687
-IS THAT?

30:19.818 --> 30:22.124
-THE KEY TO EVERY
LIFEGUARD'S DREAM.

30:22.255 --> 30:23.647
-THE TIMING COULDN'T BE BETTER.

30:24.300 --> 30:29.131
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYS]

31:05.951 --> 31:11.043
-♪ AIN'T HARD TO FIGURE OUT
WHAT THIS LIFE IS ALL ABOUT ♪

31:11.173 --> 31:16.178
♪ NOT JUST A FANTASY
THAT'S WHAT YOU DO TO ME ♪

31:16.309 --> 31:21.140
♪ I'M TIRED OF PLAYING AROUND
MY HEAD UP IN THE CLOUDS ♪

31:21.270 --> 31:24.795
♪ THAT DOESN'T MATTER TO ME

31:25.971 --> 31:31.890
♪ EVERY TIME I LOOK AROUND
BABE YOU KNOW IT'S YOU THAT I SEE ♪

31:32.716 --> 31:34.718
♪ CAN'T YOU SEE?

31:39.245 --> 31:41.769
♪ THAT I'M IN HEAVEN

31:42.857 --> 31:46.165
♪ WHEN YOU CALL MY NAME

31:47.906 --> 31:50.125
-BAYWATCH
HEADQUARTERS TO SCARAB ONE.

31:51.692 --> 31:54.956
-YEAH, THIS IS SCARAB ONE,
BEN, TEST LOUD AND CLEAR.

31:55.087 --> 31:57.828
-NO TEST. SONAR'S
PICKING UP A LARGE OBJECT

31:57.959 --> 32:00.005
TRAVELING UNDERWATER
NORTHEASTERLY DIRECTION

32:00.135 --> 32:01.180
TWO MILES OFF POINT DUME.

32:01.310 --> 32:02.355
-WE'RE ON IT.

32:02.485 --> 32:04.574
HIT IT. LET'S TRY THIS BABY OUT.

32:04.705 --> 32:07.795
-♪ AND MY HEART'S IN FLAMES

32:09.710 --> 32:12.147
♪ WITH NO DISCRETION

32:12.278 --> 32:16.369
♪ LOVE ME ONCE THEN DO IT AGAIN

32:32.602 --> 32:33.734
-THERE IT IS.

32:34.474 --> 32:36.911
-IT'S MOVING TOO FAST
TO BE A WHALE OR A SHARK.

32:37.042 --> 32:37.956
-YEAH.

32:39.087 --> 32:40.523
THERE'S THE CAVE.

32:41.133 --> 32:43.222
WE'RE RIGHT ABOVE IT,
WHERE WALT WAS KILLED.

32:44.310 --> 32:46.268
-WHERE'D IT GO? WHAT HAPPENED?

32:46.790 --> 32:48.488
-SONAR'S FUNCTIONAL,
IT JUST DISAPPEARED.

32:49.619 --> 32:53.058
-DIDN'T DISAPPEAR.
IT WENT INTO THAT CAVE.

32:53.710 --> 32:55.974
WE'LL FIND OUT WHAT THE
HELL IT IS ONCE AND FOR ALL.

32:56.844 --> 32:58.193
-I'M GOING WITH YOU.

33:12.033 --> 33:13.295
[ELECTRONIC BEEPING]

33:15.515 --> 33:17.082
-MITCH, IT'S BACK
ON THE SCREEN.

33:18.344 --> 33:20.302
IT'S OUT OF THE CAVE.
IT'S HEADING RIGHT FOR YOU.

33:21.042 --> 33:22.826
-WHERE? I DON'T SEE ANYTHING.

33:23.392 --> 33:25.307
-MITCH, IT'S PRACTICALLY
ON TOP OF YOU.

33:26.917 --> 33:28.310
-STILL DON'T SEE IT.

33:30.486 --> 33:33.141
[FRANTIC MUSIC]

33:45.110 --> 33:47.112
[STARTLED GASP]

33:50.680 --> 33:52.117
-MITCH, WHAT'S HAPPENING?

33:53.031 --> 33:54.336
-IT'S A MINISUB!

33:54.467 --> 33:55.816
IT'S GOT DEVON IN
A HYDRAULIC CLAW.

34:04.912 --> 34:07.567
[FRANTIC MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

34:16.619 --> 34:18.534
-[STRUGGLING]

34:20.014 --> 34:21.885
-MITCH, IT'S
DIVING, WHAT'S GOING ON?

34:24.975 --> 34:26.063
-DROP THE ANCHOR.

34:27.239 --> 34:29.632
HURRY! DEVON CAN'T
TAKE THE PRESSURE.

34:30.851 --> 34:32.244
-ANCHOR COMING DOWN.

34:45.953 --> 34:48.782
-OKAY, RAISE
THE ANCHOR! FULL POWER!

34:48.911 --> 34:51.871
[STEADY ELECTRONIC BEEPING]

34:55.614 --> 34:58.444
[STRUGGLING GROANS]

35:06.060 --> 35:07.714
[MECHANICAL SCREECH]

35:35.002 --> 35:38.440
[GASPING]

35:39.963 --> 35:41.922
-ARE YOU OKAY?
ARE YOU BOTH ALL RIGHT?

35:42.052 --> 35:43.663
-YEAH, I'M FINE!

35:43.793 --> 35:46.318
-YES! WHAT ABOUT THEM?

35:46.448 --> 35:47.928
-I'VE ALERTED THE COAST GUARD

35:48.058 --> 35:49.669
TO EXPECT A SPECIAL
DELIVERY PACKAGE.

35:49.799 --> 35:51.975
[PLEASED LAUGHTER]

36:08.166 --> 36:12.039
-NO OTHER OFFICE QUITE
LIKE IT, IS THERE, CAPTAIN?

36:13.736 --> 36:15.085
-IT'S A BEAUTIFUL THING.

36:35.497 --> 36:37.499
-WOULD YOU CARE TO
MAKE A STATEMENT?

36:40.285 --> 36:41.982
-THESE CHARGES
AGAINST ME AS ABSURD

36:42.112 --> 36:44.376
AS THE MONSTER IN
THE BAY NONSENSE.

36:44.941 --> 36:47.335
-IT WASN'T NONSENSE,
MR. VAN ALDEN.

36:47.466 --> 36:50.425
THERE WAS A MONSTER
IN THE BAY. YOU.

36:53.907 --> 36:57.954
[LAUGHTER]

36:59.217 --> 37:03.177
[CHILDREN PLAYING]

37:06.136 --> 37:07.747
-YOU DESERVE ONE
OF THOSE MEDALS.

37:07.877 --> 37:09.879
-ME? NO WAY.

37:10.010 --> 37:12.795
-YES, YOU DO. FOR
PUTTING UP WITH ME.

37:13.535 --> 37:15.276
HERE, I THOUGHT
YOU MIGHT WANT TO

37:15.407 --> 37:17.365
CHECK IT FOR ACCURACY, MAKE
SURE YOU WEREN'T MISQUOTED.

37:17.496 --> 37:20.760
-[LAUGHS] I'M SURE IT'S A
HELL OF A STORY.

37:21.456 --> 37:24.024
LISTEN, I REALLY HOPE YOU
GET THAT JOB AT THE TIMES.

37:25.286 --> 37:28.507
-WELL, I THOUGHT I'D DO
MY INVESTIGATIVE REPORTING

37:28.637 --> 37:30.291
ON A MORE INTIMATE LEVEL.

37:30.422 --> 37:33.120
YOU KNOW, OPEN UP MY OWN
LITTLE COMMUNITY NEWSPAPER.

37:33.251 --> 37:34.600
WHICH DO YOU THINK IS BEST?

37:34.730 --> 37:38.081
THE VENICE VOICE OR
THE PACIFIC PRESS.

37:38.212 --> 37:39.431
-YOU DECIDE.

37:41.302 --> 37:42.651
-MISSED ME.

37:42.782 --> 37:44.305
-VAN ALDEN DIDN'T
WANT TO GAMBLE ON WHICH

37:44.436 --> 37:46.873
OIL LEASES TO BID ON SO HE
BEGAN ILLEGALLY DRILLING

37:47.003 --> 37:48.962
TO LOCATE THE RICHEST DEPOSITS.

37:49.571 --> 37:51.834
WHEN WALT ACCIDENTALLY
DISCOVERED THEM,
THEY KILLED HIM.

37:53.053 --> 37:54.881
-SO, WHO'S THE MONSTER HUNTER?

37:55.011 --> 37:57.927
-OH, TADASHI. HE
DESIGNED THE SUB.

37:58.058 --> 38:00.365
VAN ALDEN ORDERED HIM
TO SINK THE FISHING BOAT

38:00.495 --> 38:03.193
TO LEAD OUR INVESTIGATION
AWAY FROM THEIR DRILLING.

38:03.890 --> 38:05.283
TADASHI CAME TO
HEADQUARTERS TO FIND OUT

38:05.413 --> 38:06.762
IF THEY'D GOTTEN AWAY WITH IT.

38:09.461 --> 38:10.940
-THANK YOU ALL FOR COMING.

38:12.246 --> 38:17.207
LA COUNTY LIFEGUARDS SAVED
10,966 LIVES LAST YEAR,

38:17.904 --> 38:20.080
AND WERE ONLY AWARDED
TWO MEDALS OF VALOR.

38:20.602 --> 38:23.649
SO, AS YOU CAN SEE,
THIS AWARD IS ONLY GIVEN

38:23.779 --> 38:26.434
TO PEOPLE WHO DISPLAY
EXTREME HEROISM.

38:26.565 --> 38:29.655
RIGHT NOW I'D LIKE TO
INTRODUCE CAPTAIN DON THORPE,

38:29.785 --> 38:32.440
WHO HAS DECIDED, FOR
ALL THE RIGHT REASONS,

38:32.571 --> 38:34.312
TO STAY HERE WITH
US ON THE BEACH.

38:34.442 --> 38:35.487
[APPLAUSE]

38:35.617 --> 38:36.575
-THANK YOU, MITCH.

38:37.619 --> 38:39.317
THANK YOU, EVERYONE,
BUT PLEASE, PLEASE,

38:39.447 --> 38:42.232
SAVE YOUR APPLAUSE FOR A
LIFEGUARD WHO'S EARNED IT.

38:43.233 --> 38:46.019
HERE TO PRESENT THE MEDAL OF
VALOR TO TODAY'S RECIPIENT

38:46.149 --> 38:48.108
IS A FORMER MEDAL OF
VALOR WINNER HIMSELF.

38:48.804 --> 38:52.808
IT'S MY GREAT PLEASURE
TO INTRODUCE TO YOU
LT. BEN EDWARDS.

38:52.939 --> 38:56.334
[APPLAUSE]

38:59.467 --> 39:03.123
-THANK YOU, CAPTAIN.
PRETTY PROUD DAY FOR ME.

39:04.037 --> 39:06.169
NOT ONLY AM I STANDING
UP HERE WITH THE BRASS,

39:06.300 --> 39:10.173
BUT AS YOUR NEW LIEUTENANT,
IT'S MY PRIVILEGE

39:10.783 --> 39:13.351
TO PRESENT THIS
YEAR'S MEDAL OF VALOR

39:14.308 --> 39:16.571
TO LIFEGUARD SHAUNI MCCLAIN!

39:16.702 --> 39:20.706
[APPLAUSE]

39:23.578 --> 39:25.145
-MITCH, WOULD YOU DO
THE HONORS, PLEASE?

39:25.275 --> 39:26.102
-SURE.

39:26.233 --> 39:29.192
[TRIUMPHANT MUSIC]

39:36.156 --> 39:39.812
I'M PROUD OF YOU.
CONGRATULATIONS.

39:39.942 --> 39:42.597
[APPLAUSE CONTINUES]

39:48.908 --> 39:54.087
-UM, THANK YOU.
I WAS JUST DOING MY JOB.

39:56.568 --> 39:57.395
-I LOVE YOU.

39:57.525 --> 39:58.657
-I LOVE YOU, TOO.

39:58.787 --> 40:01.747
[APPLAUSE CONTINUES]

40:21.288 --> 40:26.336
[ENDING THEME PLAYS]
